message: Luther never attacks Jews or Judaism on ethnic grounds. Thus, it is not antisemitic. But it most certainly is anti-Jewish. See Heiko Oberman "The Roots of Anti-Semitism: In the Age of Renaissance and Reformation"
Luther was never a monk. A friar and a monk are not the same thing.
/* At Wartburg Castle */ There is no such thing as an "Augustinian monk." They were friars.
/* Monastic and academic life */ He wasn't a monk. He was a friar. He often said he lived "like" a monk. But he never took monastic vows and never joined a monastery. He was a friar.
He was an Augustinian friar, not a monk.
/* Biblical origin */ The adjectival form is not capitalized.
The adjectival form is not capitalized.

Professor Ordinaire does not carry any of the "ordinary" connotations in the French that it does in the English. His current position is far more prestigious than his previous one. No need to foreground his notability.

Reformation Europe is NOT the Protestant Reformation. It is a much broader category.
